biography.text:
Electronic music enthusiasts worldwide recognize Dimitri ‘Vegas’ Thivaios as one-half of the formidable brotherly duo, ‘Dimitri Vegas & Like Mike’ and as the ambassador of the global sensation Tomorrowland. These brothers have become electronic music superstars, capturing the adoration of audiences across the globe. With a social media following of over 30 million fans, coupled with billions of music streams and video views showcasing their extravagant live performances and music videos, their impact is undeniable.

After a remarkable ascent in the music scene over the years, Dimitri Vegas reached new heights in 2015 and 2019 when he and his brother were crowned DJ Mag’s No.1 DJs in the world. Maintaining a global top 5 position for nine consecutive years in the prestigious list, they have also earned various MTV EMA awards and numerous other international accolades.

Accumulating more Gold and Platinum records than he can keep track of, Dimitri Vegas, along with his brother, has garnered admiration from icons across genres.

Beyond his established career as an electronic music artist, Dimitri has wholeheartedly embraced acting in recent years, actively engaging in writing, producing and even directing. Notable achievements include starring in Jurassic World Dominion and taking on the lead role in the film H4Z4RD, while also lending his image and voice for videogames like Mortal Kombat, Hitman and Free Fire.
